pending on the supplies of food. They tend to fly short distances and low to the ground with great strength. Breeding occurs in spring and summer. The nest is a flat platform of sticks and vines, either in a fork of a tree or on top of a low tree. One, creamy white, egg is laid. Subspecies M. d. doreya Bonaparte, 1854 - western New Guinea and western Papuan islands M. d. balim Rand, 1941 - Balim Valley, north central New Guinea M. d. albiceps Bonaparte, 1856 - northern Moluccas M. d. atrata Ripley, 1941 - Togian Island M. d. sanghirensis Salvadori, 1878 - Sangihe Islands and Talaud Islands M. d. albicapilla Bonaparte, 1854 - Sulawesi M. d. sedecima Neumann, 1939 - Sula Islands References Further reading", "shortSummary": "Sultan's cuckoo-dove (Macropygia doreya) is a dove in the genus Macropygia found in the northern Moluccas, Sulawesi to New Guinea and the w…", "locations": ["北苏拉威西省", "摩鹿加群岛", "新幾內亞島", "巴布亚省"], "lat": 1.25, "lng": 124.83333333, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Macropygia_amboinensis_-_Mount_Mahawu_%282%29.JPG/960px-Macropygia_amboinensis_-_Mount_Mahawu_%282%29.JPG", "order": "Columbiformes", "family": "Columbidae", "genus": "Macropygia", "species": "Macropygia doreya", "orderCn": "鸽形目", "familyCn": "鸠鸽科", "genusCn": "鹃鸠属", "speciesCn": "Sultan's cuckoo-dove", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-macropygia", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-macropygia-doreya", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-macropygia", "species": "taxonomy-species-macropygia-doreya"}, "expandable": true, "x": -946.72, "y": 5.5, "z": -77.44}], "links": [{"key": 